 Makhanda - Police in Makhanda have appealed to the public for assistance with information that can hep them find a missing woman. "Joza SAPS are searching for Ndileka Tshunungwa, who went missing after she was discharged from a local Hospital after she was being treated for epilepsy," described police spokesperson, Captain Mali Govender. "She left the hospital on Tuesday at approximately 17:00 and has not returned home or contacted her family." Capt Govender said that Tshunungwa is 45 years old and resides in Lingelihle Location, Ext 6 Joza, in Mkhanda. "She was last seen was wearing a multi-coloured skirt, blue jacket and white doek." Any person, who can assist in locating her can Contact their local SAPS or her daughter Thandokazi Tshunungwana on 074 9053 262. Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 